    • Method Detail

      • performAction

        protected boolean performAction(org.newdawn.slick.GameContainer gc,
                                org.newdawn.slick.state.StateBasedGame sb,
                                int delta)
        checks if the action(s) associated with this event shall be performed. In this case, the action(s) are only performed if an collision between the entity that own this event object and a different entity has taken place.
        Specified by:
        performAction in class eea.engine.event.Event
        Parameters:
        gc - the GameContainer object that handles the game loop, recording of the frame rate, and managing the input system
        sb - the StateBasedGame that isolates different stages of the game (e.g., menu, ingame, highscores etc.) into different states so they can be easily managed and maintained.
        delta - the time passed in nanoseconds (ns) since the start of the event, used to interpolate the current target position
        Returns:
        true if the action(s) associated with this event shall be performed, else false
